author: Palmer, Bill (2004) Uruava dictionary, Additions from Piet Lincoln
notes: Palmer's dictionary is an exhaustive compilation from older sources. Uruava is an extinct language of Bougainville. Missing items are probably lost for ever.
problems: Sources diagree as to whether Palmers <g> represents [g] or [ŋ]. Palmer assumes [g].
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Central-Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Eastern Malayo-Polynesian, Oceanic, Western Oceanic, Meso Melanesian, New Ireland, South New Ireland-Northwest Solomonic, Mono-Uruava
